data.content:
Here are the two files:

**`SortableList.razor`** — the markup with a `@typeparam TItem` directive. Each item renders the caller's `ItemTemplate`, plus Move Up/Down buttons. Buttons are disabled at the list boundaries. `@key` is used for efficient diffing.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — the `partial class` code-behind:

- **`Items`** (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) — the source list, never mutated.
- **`_items`** — internal copy, created in `OnParametersSet`.
- **`ItemTemplate`** (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) — the caller's template.
- **`OnOrderChanged`** (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) — fires after each swap, passing a read-only snapshot.

Usage matches your example:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
